    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@wadelee1986 You can interact with an existing contract within Solidity if you have its deployed address and its source code There's a nice tutorial about how to do this [here](https://dappsforbeginners.wordpress.com/tutorials/interactions-between-contracts/)\r\n\r\n**Example**\r\n```javascript\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.18;\r\n\r\ncontract HelloToken {\r\n  event SaidHello(address caller);\r\n\r\n  function hello() public {\r\n    emit SaidHello(msg.sender);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Caller {\r\n  function callHelloToken(address deployed) public {\r\n     HelloToken token = HelloToken(deployed); // Get HelloToken instance at some address\r\n     token.hello(); // Use token contract\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nClosing because this is a question about how to use the Solidity language rather than a problem specific to Truffle. ",
